Surprised nobody here nor on the reddit thread caught this one: https://github.com/nahla-nee/wfqueue/blob/main/src/lib.rs#L3...
    unsafe impl Sync for WFQueue {}
    unsafe impl Send for WFQueue {}

These impls are unsound, because neither constrains `T` to be `Sync`/`Send`. As-written this would let you declare a `WFQueue, N>` and pass non-atomic-refcount pointers between threads.
The fix is straightforward:
    unsafe impl Sync for WFQueue {}
    unsafe impl Send for WFQueue {}

I.e., WFQueue is only Sync if T is Sync, and likewise for Send.
Actually, later on, the code makes a similar mistake, but only for one impl.
    unsafe impl Send for DrivableWFEnqueue where T: Send {}
    unsafe impl Send for DrivableWFDequeue {}
